The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter OFFICER commanding police in Matabeleland North Commissioner Erasmus Makodza who is facing charges of corruptly concealing a transaction from a principal has been released on $10 000 bail. Comm Makodza appeared today before Harare regional magistrate Mr Stanley Mambanje facing corruption charges. He was remanded to March 2. He was ordered to report once a month and not interfere with witnesses as part of the bail conditions. Mrs Netsai Mushayabasa appeared for the State while lawyer Mr Tapiwa Makanza represented Makodza